				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				&gt; The only ones that have a problem with this<BR>
&gt; is the ones that dont play by the rules<BR>
<BR>
This kind of mentality is at the root of all evil empires. Personally, I have nothing to hide, so I don't mind Verant looking for ShowEQ or whatever hacking program that comes out next. However, what if Verant just doesn't like the program I have for parsing EQ logs?<BR>
<BR>
I do have a problem with Verant's view on selling EQ accounts. While I, personally, would never stoop to buying someone else's character, and I find paying $$ for a BIBS, etc. absurd, if a person wishes to do so, there is technically (and legally) nothing Verant can do about it (and this fact has already been determined in a court of law).<BR>
<BR>
Furthermore, there is also some issue as to whether or not the license agreement applies to everyone in all states and countries. There are some states already that do not find internet contracts binding, and force companies to &quot;get it in writing&quot; before they can bind their customers to them. I'm sure the same can be said for other countries.
