				I know there are alot of opinions here and mine will probably be redundant but I feel compelled to say something.<BR>
<BR>
EBay - I could care less.  I don't understand why people actually buy and sell game items on E-Bay.  The actual character sales for thousands has me baffled beyond belief.  Honestly though I could care less, it is thier money (as big a waste as I think it is).  An excellent point posted though, EBayers are selling the property of Verant and that can be questioned morally.  Will Verant's new EULA stop the selling of accounts and items?  Honestly, I don't think they can, short of banning everyone they can prove is involved with this.<BR>
<BR>
The inspection of my PC is outrageous.  I do not use ShowEQ (wouldn't know how if I wanted to)and I really don't care if John Doe uses it.  As long as my gameplay is not interrupted I don't care.  Smedly states that Verant will only look at the Everquest directory, then that needs to be added to the EULA as well as his statement of not scanning the Registry.  <BR>
<BR>
While I dont think of myself as a person who is paranoid or thinks conspiracies are everywhere, I do value my privacy.  All Im asking for is some clarification in the EULA, I want to be assured in the EULA that I have to agree to everytime I log in, that my privacy is mine and if Verant gets a wild hair and violates that privacy, then someone will answer for the violation.<BR>
<BR>
I apologize, I know this is long but I wanted to be heard.  <BR>
