	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I too am a bit concerned over Verant's decision to allow itself to obtain certain information from our computers.  As far as downloading data and comparing filesizes with their database, that's fine.  However, looking through our EverQuest directory for files other than their own is a problem.  Viewing the personal files of their users is an immense violation of the users' privacy.  It will undoutedly cause many EverQuest players to leave the game.<BR>
<BR>
As far as the selling of characters/items for personal profit is concerned, I support their actions to try to stop this.  EverQuest, and everything involved with it, is the sole property of Verant.  Anyone who profits from the game is obligated to share a part of the profit with Verant.  It is illegal to use someone else's property for profit, without expressed consent from the owner.  Anyone selling characters, etc, is profiting from Verant's property.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
