	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is almost unreal here. I have to say I never thought to see this. I have played many a game, especially role-playing games. I never gave EQ a try till about two weeks ago because the whole idea of having to pay for the account AND pay for the game seemed absurd. The thing that floored me was that people were selling the stuff on Ebay for real money, which when a friend showed me this, I said, okay, cool; the game must be superb.<BR>
<BR>
I went out and bought the game and got pretty hooked on it. Whether I would be able to get high enough level to be able to offer stuff on Ebay was a question I knew not the answer to, but the whole idea of it was so far out there I had to try. I got my brother to get the game and an account, and I got a friend to as well. Odds are, we'd not have made it that high, but the idea of trying was great. And I'd have never even given it a try if not for the Ebay craze.<BR>
<BR>
What strikes me as absurd is that this kind of thing HAS to be making Verant money. Think about it. The internet &quot;marketeers&quot; out there have to be playing the game with accounts, making verant money. The people unable or unwilling (or maybe just without the time) to get high level themselves that are willing to pay for these things would be making money for Verant by using accounts, the publicity of the whole idea, done properly, could have generated tons of new people. Etc. With this act of stupidity though, they will alienate the marketeers, the buyers, Diablo 2 will likely blow it away now, and a perfect opportunity of advertising has been utterly wasted.<BR>
<BR>
I know, I know; the purists say &quot;good riddance&quot; to ebayers. Bt think about it, that added element brought in even more diverse types and personalities. The kind of thing that seperates a good game from a great gaming experience. Personally, after getting a Wizard to 8th lvl and loving every minute of it, would I want to group with an externally good character only to find it's a newbie in sheep's clothing (Ebay buyer). Heck no; but the experience of finding it out the hard way would be an everlasting memory one wouldn't forget.<BR>
<BR>
The sad thing is, it will still happen. You know it will, but now, people will end up paying more since it isn't allowed. Plus, the ones paying will be taken in all the more because there will be NO policing the legit deals. At least on Ebay, if someone is cheated, the person doing the cheating will get bad reviews and not cheat as many others. Anyways, I am not seeing posts from this point of view and I think it's a shame. Just because you play a certain way and earned your character levels and money and items doesn't mean everyone should have to to be able to play. That's like saying everyone has to be a certain way or thnk a certain way... We use races in the game, but that is the sort of attitude that's almost &quot;racist&quot;; which is something entirely different. It's a sad day in EQ.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
